data.description: Chinese and Thai restaurant Stir fried sea crab with curry powder tom yum kung dimsum Hua Seng Hong has been chosen by Lonely Planet Traveller Thailand as one of the restaurants on their 50 Legends of Taste list. The restaurant which has been around for half a century began serving its patrons in Yaowarat district or Chinatown, the area well-known for Bangkok's famous good eats. At Hua Seng Hong, our heartfelt commitment to quality and value for customers has been handed down from generation to generation. From what started in Yaowarat half a century ago, we now have 19 branches in Bangkok. Our wide variety of menu range from Chinese, Thai, seafood, hot pot, and one dish meals, to Hong Kong noodles and dim sum. We have over 200 delicious dishes await you at one of Thailand's 50 Legends of Taste.

data.name: Hong Kong Fisherman
data.description: Hong Kong Fisherman is one of Bangkok’s best Chinese restaurants specializing in Cantonese cuisine. You will be spoilt for choice with a wide array of delightful culinary delicacies created and prepared by our renowned Hong Kong chefs, featuring over 200 authentic menus which include 50 kinds of Hong Kong dim sum, noodle dishes, hot pots and slow-cooked soups. Additionally, you can also enjoy the very best of freshly baked Hong Kong-style dessert. The restaurant was designed in imitation of Victoria Harbour in Hong Kong with an elegant decoration in modern Chinese style inspired by the Old Shanghai period. There is no need to travel to Hong Kong anymore as you can now experience the real taste of Cantonese cuisine at Hong Kong Fisherman here in Thailand.
